	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002257_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<!--Hand 01 51 top left--><!--Hand 02 56118 top right--><!-- Hand 03 <p>&quot;M<hi rend="superscript"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Walker Brodie</p><p>29, Park Road,</p><p>Haverstock Hill,</p><p>London. N.W.&quot;</p> top left-->
<lb/><p rend="right">Newstead Abbey</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">7 April 1865</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p>On searching 
<lb/>for the address you 
<lb/>requested, I find 
<lb/>that I cannot lay 
<lb/>my hands on it. 
<lb/>A young man in 
<lb/>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Hamilton's church 
<lb/>Regent's Square 
<lb/>London told me 
<lb/>about M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Silva's 
<lb/>proposed visit 
<lb/>&amp; said that on his 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002257_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>arrival he would 
<lb/>let me know. The 
<lb/>young man gave 
<lb/>me his card but 
<lb/>expecting him to 
<lb/>communicate I 
<lb/>took no care of it</p>
<lb/><p>From your 
<lb/>further explanations 
<lb/>it seems that 
<lb/>you do not so 
<lb/>much need the 
<lb/>information 
<lb/>that M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Silva can 
<lb/>give. No obstacle 
<lb/>will be made 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002257_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/>or put in the way of 
<lb/>a settler, but I question 
<lb/>whether he could 
<lb/>take notes of 
<w>testa-<lb break="no"/>ments</w> through the 
<lb/>custom house at 
<lb/>the beginning of 
<lb/>his <choice><sic>carreer</sic><corr>career</corr></choice>. When 
<lb/>a person is known 
<lb/>to the officers they 
<lb/>are not so illiberal. 
<lb/>Your plan seems 
<lb/>more feasible 
<lb/>now than it did 
<lb/>at first and I 
<lb/>trust that the 
<lb/>Highest will 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002257_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/>prosper your work 
<lb/>I should be glad if 
<lb/>at any future time 
<lb/>you will let me 
<lb/>know how you 
<lb/>get on in it. By 
<lb/>consulting the Foreign 
<lb/>Office list you 
<lb/>might find out 
<lb/>who is the Commissioner 
<lb/>or Arbiter on the 
<lb/>English side at 
<lb/><unclear cert="low">Soanda</unclear> &amp; make 
<lb/>enquiries about him 
<lb/>to see if he is likely to 
<lb/>be favourable or 
<lb/>otherwise I am &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">David Livingstone</p>
			
